<TITLE> Ministry announces SSC, HSC exam schedules </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 19 (bdnews24.com)- The Secondary School Certificate and equivalent examinations have been scheduled for Feb 28, 2008 while the Higher Secondary Certificate and equivalent examinations begin on April 29 the same year, according to a handout issued Tuesday. SSC and equivalent examinations for 2009 will start on Feb 15 while the HSC and equivalent examinations on April 15, the education ministry said in the handout. Public relations officer for the ministry Subodh Chandra Dhali told bdnews24.com that the government had also fixed the date for publication of results. The results of SSC and equivalent examinations, 2008 will be published on June 8 while those of the HSC and equivalent exams on Aug 10. In 2009, the results of the examinations will be published on May 25 and July 25 respectively. The handout said that from 2010 the SSC and equivalent examinations would start on Feb 1 every year while the HSC and equivalent exams, on April 1. Every year the SSC results will be published on May 10 while those of HSC on July 10. The government has already issued a circular in this regard. The circular said that if the examinations could not be started due to any unavoidable circumstances, it would start the next day or on any convenient closest day. The Inter-education board chairman will prepare a work plan from the start of the examinations and the publication of the results. It will specify who will do which task at which time. The two national examinations will be completed in the possible minimum time so that the examinees face no extra pressure. The handout mentioned that as a result, the examiners would get sufficient time to evaluate the answer scripts. bdnews
